cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at| Hi Everyone and welcome to today's session, in which we'll be continuing a look at Doubles.

Last time we looked at a variety of non-penalty doubles, including negative, competitive, support and 4th-suit doubles.

This week we're only going to look at 2 sorts of doubles, both of which are only used at very high level competitive auctions and both of which in different ways, help partner to decide whether or not to bid one more.

Although we are only looking at 2 types of double this week, they are more difficult to understand and you absolute MUST be on the same wavelength as partner (ie: they need discussion).

Having said that they are both VERY useful devices to have in your arsenal.

These are NOT something you can hope to play with a pick-up partner, because they likely won't have the faintest idea what you're talking about.  

If you have not already done so, please have a look at the notes I have prepared on tonight's topic.

You can find these on: ^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/index.php ^*n

The section on Doubles can be accessed directly at ^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/Doubles.php ^*n|
