cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   Hopefully those two examples have shown you both sides of the coin.

Control-denying (aka Showing) doubles can really help you to avoid selling out to a cheap sacrifice when you can make one more, and to avoid getting too high when settling for a penalty is the better option.

Please remember the conditions that must be met before Control-denying (aka Showing) doubles kick in.

