cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|     So what is a defensive trick?

Well not always easy to be absolutely certain (life would be too easy otherwise).

Aces are usually a fair bet except in YOUR suit, especially if you think you have a 10-card or better trump fit your way.

Combinations such as QJx or J109x in THEIR suit are a good bet, especially if it's likely that their trump honours are split.

Honour cards in side-suits that seem to be well-placed, bearing in mind Opps' bidding, might also be counted.

You cannot usually count on getting ruffs unless it's in a suit that partner has shown some strength in.

Aces and Kings are more useful than Queens and Jacks here.

